HEADWORD: Retake
<hw>Re*take"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
take or receive again.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take from a captor; to recapture; <as>as, to
<ex>retake</ex> a ship or prisoners</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retaker</ent>⟦br⟧
